</p></sec><sec id="sec2706"><title>Conclusions</title><p>During the COVID-19 outbreak, healthcare systems, including those in Taiwan, were tested for unparalleled service challenges. This study found that while outpatient services boosted profits, rising inpatient admissions strained finances, given their higher costs and staffing needs. After the pandemic, psychiatric departments should reconsider resource allocation to balance expenses and revenues. Effective management is crucial for patient outcomes, emphasizing the need for quality care and fiscal control. Future research must focus on fortifying healthcare resilience.</p></sec><sec id="sec2707"><title>Disclosure of Interest</title><p>None Declared</p></sec></abstract><counts><page-count count="1"/></counts></article-meta></front></article>